commit 3f82f9999c1de42225f6e091bc3ce6e48c089ddb
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Tue Jul 2 15:10:09 2024 -0400

    Set importer attribute on stl-g BoT solids

commit 7ecf01ce0a72275e5d863d3d08f55e63737c0954
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Tue Jul 2 15:01:42 2024 -0400

    Update stl-g object naming
    
    Use some of the VLS simplification and cleanup routines we've developed over
    the years to improve stl-g object naming.  Also, per user request, skipping
    text inside < > bracketing when making object names.
    
    Switching solid and region names from using prefix (s. and r.) to suffix (.s
    and .r) naming conventions.  These extensions are often viewed similarly to
    filename extensions (and using suffixes has the advantage of allowing
    bu_path_component to break down the names as well.)

commit 09824e622aa8449de10ae2349e9a203c4f03c18b
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Tue Jul 2 11:19:15 2024 -0400

    Adjust 3dm-g import attribute for consistency,clarity
    
    Josh asked if we could make the attribute assigned when importing geometry
    consistent - Creo plugin is using importer, so let's go with that for 3dm-g as
    well.  Also, store the name of the converter and don't use spaces in the value.

