commit 1a28cfb78f083cf83a323c7512e239fafec07aaa
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Fri Jun 28 18:49:26 2024 -0400

    Validate function pointer is non-NULL

commit 8905498040a0df1be32d5c685617fb92cbc82ccb
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Fri Jun 28 11:28:20 2024 -0400

    Fix filter return settings for search -or case
    
    Chris noticed a problem with the db_search return value when using the
    -or filter - numerical return values were order dependent.  Bookkeeping
    of the return values in the f_or loop processing was incorrect - we were
    zeroing out if the last filter didn't match, when what we need to do is
    track if any of the filters was successful and report accordingly.

commit a028ae8d47367611e73023a7ba0b5a72ef665d45
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Thu Jun 27 15:57:01 2024 -0400

    Grr.  GCC 12 doesn't seem to be properly respecting the multiple pragma diagnostic calls

