commit 8cb4d093773418f342cfa0a863955db0847fa81c
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Mon Jun 17 09:58:08 2024 -0400

    Fix comment

commit 0af151b27ce379bb14e74e64d6a74c95e2ae7550
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Fri Jun 14 20:35:34 2024 -0400

    Validate the repair results, only use clean output
    
    The bot repair routine doesn't always manage to produce an output that
    satisfies the thin bots check, even when it produces a manifold output.
    Check the repaired output, and only replace the original manifold result
    with the new BoT when it passes the thin faces check.  Note in the
    verbose log what happened.
    
    We need to be more aggressive in the librt routine - filtering out
    first-hit misses results in our not seeing some problems that the repair
    routine can handle (the havoc windows are a case in point.)

commit be376bc3e228ec0496585fbd65dbd92e83f4491b
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Fri Jun 14 14:47:58 2024 -0400

    We want to write to the file immediately, in case something goes wrong.

commit 5ff3c7b76a7ae591c5fb5a473b0feb2704d7ec68
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Fri Jun 14 14:36:32 2024 -0400

    If we're resuming a conversion, we'll want to append rather than overwrite the log

commit 6574ff66c513d607c21c218163285e656430dfb7
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Fri Jun 14 14:35:58 2024 -0400

    Add a way to turn off the bot_fixup step - in case the repair logic has trouble with an input, we need a way to skip it and get whatever output the other routines can generate.  Even if it's not usable as-is, the unaltered output may be the best starting point for repair work.

