commit 9646922ddcaff307fab31c91c885f366fb8340e0
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Fri May 31 14:54:13 2024 -0400

    Support nuanced controls for specifying lint methods.
    
    Added support for optional technique specifiers to lint -I option.  It's not
    required, but if specific techniques are specified only those will be used for
    testing.  Goal is to allow visualization of specific categories of BoT problem
    faces.

commit 4d053744cec8d072a971a40dbad3c5cf27efacf1
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Fri May 31 11:22:16 2024 -0400

    Add a visualize option to lint
    
    We want to be able to see where the problem triangles in a mesh are, and we
    have enough information from the raytrace to be able to do so.  Set up a
    -V option for lint to allow plotting of problematic faces.
    
    Ideally we probably want the -I option to lint to allow for more specialization
    - i.e., only run one specific type of BoT check, for example.  This will need
    some sort of flexible test specification mechanism.

commit 458558bcc89f88d33453e723867df8b4750d07e3
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Thu May 30 20:53:48 2024 -0400

    Rough in bot plot subcommand
    
    For now this is just plotting faces by index.  Need to think about
    whether it makes sense to support plotting vertices as well - that might
    be less useful, since if we can retrieve a vertex's coordinates by index
    it would be trivial to either move the view center to that point or make
    a sphere there...
    
    On a related note - probably need to adjust the bot get syntax. Right
    now it's property then objname, but if we want to upgrade it to allow
    getting per face and per vertex info we need the property to optionally
    have arguments - that would make more sense in a "bot get objname prop
    [opt]" layout.

