commit c8b4e8ca365e239cc8c3d52e8da17fc8a93092bc
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Tue May 28 20:06:27 2024 -0400

    Set up libged lint cmd versions of checks
    
    We're going to want more powerful reporting and visualization than makes
    sense for librt.  Reduce the bot check there to just the one facetize
    uses, and shift the more extensive logic into lint.  If we want to set
    up for things like json logging, visualization of problem triangles,
    etc. it makes more sense to do it in the lint command rather than trying
    to shoehorn it into the librt API, at least in the early stages.  If
    something emerges that makes sense in librt we can move it back later.

