commit 2b18a179455b78c5a8ee63a93b7a6242a2f467f6
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Wed May 15 22:51:34 2024 -0400

    Ah, right - the LoD drawing test does test shaded drawing of a brep, and the detria change causes off-by-1 img differences.

commit e2909c45e810ed3653c9d837d648ac335b26be1f
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Wed May 15 19:04:55 2024 -0400

    Replace poly2tri with detria
    
    This logic is exposed via the e -m1 shaded drawing and brep->bot
    facetization routines.  The latter aren't working for most inputs at the
    moment with either triangulator (need to fix that, but that logic is a
    deep dive so it will have to be later).  However, testing a couple of
    basic primitive->brep->bot conversions confirms we ARE able to get
    triangles out with the new detria logic in this pipeline when the
    inputs aren't problematic for other reasons.
    
    More significant at the moment is the use of this triangulation for
    interactive shaded display of NURBS brep geometry, and in testing so far
    the speed appears to be on the same order as poly2tri and the results
    are either comparable or (in a couple of cases) actually better. A
    conversion of the GrabCAD model YachtMod(55).3dm resulted in inputs that
    resulted in the poly2tri-backed draw crashing but the detria-backed draw
    succeeding.
    
    Give detria appears to *fix* a drawing problem, that's motivation for
    switching it in.  Although not decisive in and of itself, another
    convenient benefit of this switch will be eliminating the need for our
    forked copy of poly2tri (we have diverged from upstream, and the last
    attempt at using vanilla upstream poly2tri resulted in unsuccessful
    shading results for various NURBS surfaces.)

commit c55ec15b6b3ac85a05b91204ffb58ccfa75adf8c
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Wed May 15 17:46:15 2024 -0400

    Fix tclIndex and pkgIndex input collections
    
    Use global properties to collect the dependency and install lists for
    the index generation.  Also, fail immediately if any of the indexing
    commands doesn't succeed.

