commit 7529fcb7a1542947b4240cb53419023e5d142bc9
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Tue May 14 19:05:53 2024 -0400

    Realign distcheck tests for bext build testing
    
    The enableall and autodetect settings in the original tests aren't
    directly relevant for all cases now, but they do have analogs if the
    configure process is responsible for building bext rather than re-using
    the parent supplied files.
    
    Set up some additional tests to try and cover the configure-driven bext
    cases, and explicitly pass BRLCAD_EXT_DIR for the others rather than
    hard coding it into the test templates.
    
    Also simply definition of distcheck target.  distcheck-full is what we
    use to actually test - the shorter list of configurations originally
    defined for distcheck-std is not used in practice.  If any of the
    distcheck-full configurations is broken, that identifies an issue we
    need to fix - rather than defining a macro and getting fancy, just
    specify the configurations and targets we actually use.

