commit 8d9fd80c1e0e82a391a57abf934b689a2ab2b45c
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Mon May 13 12:54:56 2024 -0400

    Rework gqa plot testing into a regression test
    
    These tests will trigger the cache logic, so rework them into a
    regression test were we can use BU_DIR_CACHE to localize the cache
    activity.
    
    This seems to be the last functional issue for make check to work (at
    least on Linux) when disabling the man user cache.  That should imply
    that the build and check process is now localized, and we won't have
    tests and multiple builds all trying to pile into the global cache at
    once.
    
    The way this was tested was 1) removing the .cache/BRL-CAD directory and
    replacing it with a file (i.e. ensuring that any attempt to work with
    the standard cache location would fail) and 2) altering cache.c in librt
    to make any failure to set up the cache immediately fatal.  If we don't
    do that, then the uncached behavior is used and everything still works -
    but for this case, we wanted specifically to identify cases where we
    didn't have localized cache logic, so we needed an immediate failure.

commit 709f0866c52d15ab2e2e20ea5ee91dd1fe30747f
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Mon May 13 12:16:48 2024 -0400

    Make sure the cache dirs are present so bu_dir will use the environment variable

