commit da3be4baac96463e1f394b41a3dee811a830e0a8
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Fri May 10 14:29:22 2024 -0400

    Do a little bit of cleanup on the distcheck tgts
    
    With bext coming online, there are some implications for distcheck.  An
    earlier commit instructed the distcheck builds to re-use the bext
    provided by the parent build, and that's an overall BIG win, but in the
    (so far theoretical) case where we try to get distcheck working on
    Windows, it won't fly due to the Debug/Release incompatibility problem.
    When the time comes we'll have to engineer so we can both reuse when
    possible and build when necessary, but for the moment we just skip
    defining the targets where we can't use them (and where they weren't
    known to be working anyway.)
    
    Also remove the bundled libs control variables - we no longer specify
    that at the BRL-CAD configure stage.
    
    Definitely more work to do here - post-build cleanup is well and truly
    busted by the bext copies, so it looks like the distclean logic didn't
    get the memo.  Also need to clean up the pkgIndex and tclIndex files
    properly after that logic was reworked.

commit a1289f492edb9e07732463b6beea10b3ab4bc17f
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Fri May 10 14:20:50 2024 -0400

    Don't do the index logic if we don't have a btclsh target

commit 1aea05ae676d54caf8fb46ca49fdc6ebe8853f88
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Fri May 10 13:38:56 2024 -0400

    regress gcv tests weren't odd-pathnames proof either.

commit 06512006469500a8fd6e9f5b5aa214230f70715e
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Fri May 10 12:49:30 2024 -0400

    Address issue with getModulePath and odd pathnames
    
    whereami.c uses sscanf to break up and parse a map file on Linux, and
    the odd pathnames test wound up detecting that the code wasn't returning
    the full path when there was a space in it (which is expected behavior
    when using %s with sscanf - it treats spaces as delimiters.)
    
    Using a hint from https://stackoverflow.com/a/50440783/2037687 we change
    this logic to instead read the full remaining contents of the line for
    the path.

commit 467c4296ff789cb5ad25382d48b9fb5044e729b3
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Fri May 10 11:30:02 2024 -0400

    If we're doing distcheck, we've already done a configure and have a BRLCAD_EXT_DIR - use it.

