commit 74f1314bfccc7804ad219dbe19e1cb620fb0c765
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Fri Apr 26 12:23:25 2024 -0400

    Add examples of using presets with BRLCAD_EXT_DIR
    
    Since it will be a recommended/common pattern to build bext once and
    reuse it many times, it will probably make sense for developers to
    utilize CMakeUserPresets.json to make the configure process smoother and
    easier to use (as opposed to having to type out the location of
    BRLCAD_EXT_DIR each time.)  Provide a couple minimalist examples of json
    files set up to do this.

commit d08f5733a641d0e1e2af6a48ed546d14596b6ff8
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Fri Apr 26 12:05:17 2024 -0400

    CMakePresets.json is apparently intended to be used for cases where project-wide setting defaults might want to be defined.  I can thing of a few cases where we might want to do that - for exmaple, it's one potential way to encode the configuration options used by the distcheck-full builds - so let's not ignore it.  Also explain a little more about where some of these ignore file patterns are coming from.

