commit 97e24cfc0cce07144e73fb30b4e31ecbb00e2ae5
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Wed Apr 24 16:57:25 2024 -0400

    Rough logic to spot between bext and CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE
    
    Given the impracticality of mixing Debug and Release binaries on
    Windows, we need a way to spot up front when we've been handed a
    BRLCAD_EXT_DIR using the wrong MSVC runtime.
    
    Untested (i.e. virtually certain to not be correct yet) but rough in
    some logic to try to detect what configuration bext was built in.

commit 94cac3ca3df980a5944de9f631c2b56cf3349699
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Wed Apr 24 15:32:31 2024 -0400

    Force all CMake generators to use one configuration
    
    With the switch to bext, the configure process (in some modes) needs to
    build bext itself.  This means with MSVC we can't switch the build type
    from Debug to Release at build time, since Debug bext binaries aren't
    usable with Release BRL-CAD build outputs and vice versa.  Even with a
    pre-defined BRLCAD_EXT_DIR, that directory will hold only one
    configuration of the bext binaries and we still won't be able to do
    a Debug/Release build time switch.
    
    If we wanted the configure process in a multiconfig build environment to
    pre-build and manage all possible configurations of bext (which can be
    as many as 4, if we use the CMake pre-defined build configurations) we
    would have a huge problem in terms of build logic complexity, disk space
    and configure time requirements as we built multiple copies of
    potentially all of bext.  This isn't worthwhile just to be able to
    select between Debug and Release at built time, when we can just set up
    two build directories to achieve the same result and avoid the whole
    problem.
    
    To constrain BRL-CAD's build to the desired behavior, we need to
    simplify what configurations are allowed for a single configure+build
    setup by overriding CMAKE_CONFIGURATION_TYPES.  As a bonus, we can also
    eliminate a lot of logic that was added specifically to support BRL-CAD
    being runnable in per-configuration build directories.  Needs to be
    tested with Visual Studio to make sure we've successfully cleared the
    old logic out correctly and set up the necessary output directory
    variable overrides to make things work like a single-config tool, but
    in the end this should be a lot easier to deal with across the board.

commit 7cdc09b488fa05ff7df2458bfc291ea9b672c1da
Author: f4alt <christopherjmacgregor@gmail.com>
