commit 148753e9250ddef30cd41604c6b851dc63488abb
Author: f4alt <christopherjmacgregor@gmail.com>
Date:   Mon Apr 22 11:56:48 2024 -0400

    make it clear process manip via pid is intentional
    
    some features, like alive checking and termination, are preferable to
    access via a process ID rather than the process struct. To make the API
    uniform, break these tools out into a new prefix: bu_pid instead of
    bu_process.
    
    Also update return and input types to pid_t for extra clarity.

