commit 5696b2042390e6d2fee464f25ee796fe64dca8fd
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Tue Apr 16 20:51:56 2024 -0400

    Make sure we have non-empty strings for the SHA1 reports

commit 58462a3702f89304f9df35e031e961ed909fc8c6
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Tue Apr 16 20:08:52 2024 -0400

    Adjust messaging based on whether src/bext is populated

commit 0286b6e72dea8678ad48438ce1bba6652f5d91de
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Tue Apr 16 19:25:49 2024 -0400

    Check to see if a populated src/bext is up to date
    
    Because git submodules always point to a specific SHA1, there's no way
    to tell src/bext to always pull the latest checkout of RELEASE when
    doing the "git clone --recurse-submodules" checkout.  Since bext and
    brlcad are decoupled, updating BRL-CAD/bext's RELEASE branch won't
    automatically update the src/bext submodule.  In order to keep the two
    in sync, in the cases where we have an internet connection validate the
    local submodule SHA1 against the bext RELEASE branch's latest SHA1.
    It's not a fatal error - we just warn if there's a mismatch and advise
    updating src/bext to point to the latest.
    
    In the case of a checkout of a release tag of BRL-CAD, src/bext should
    be pointed to the equivalent rel-X-Y-Z branch of bext rather than
    RELEASE.  Accordingly, we also check for that case if the RELEASE SHA1
    doesn't match before concluding there's a problem.

commit b6b50de1ee30fa26bda5d6e35fe9fbe7552efa8d
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Tue Apr 16 17:06:45 2024 -0400

    Set up bext as a submodule in src
    
    A default "git clone" of BRL-CAD will not populate bext, so the more
    minimal configure-driven "clone only what you need" process will still
    be the default.  However, since that requires an internet connection to
    work, we also want to make it as easy as possible to get a "full"
    checkout of all the necessary sources, and setting up a submodule will
    allow for the possibility of a "one shot clone everything" process with:
    
        git clone --recursive https://github.com/BRL-CAD/brlcad.git
    
    This will result in a large checkout, since all the Appleseed and OSPray
    dependencies will also be cloned, but it will obtain everything with one
    command.

