commit fec8f7df457065a6c2910a590a45e10761d2e6d7
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Mon Apr 15 15:06:19 2024 -0400

    Update GitHub Actions workflows for bext building
    
    Phew.  This was a lot more work than expected, but looks like we now
    have a working path for building BRL-CAD with bext-based dependencies.
    Particular considerations included:
    
    1.  Had to provide an option for configure-driven bext builds to
        operation in non-parallel mode.  Parallel building was too much
        for the runners and resulted in failures (Tcl building was
        particularly fragile for some reason.)
    2.  Qt6 - for the moment, going ahead and having bext build the subset
        of Qt that we need as part of bext building.  Should probably figure
        out how to used the cached Qt for some of the tests, but the full CI
        cycle is pretty long even without the Qt build and it is nice to know
        the full bext Qt + BRL-CAD stack is at least building across the
        various CI platforms.
    3.  Space - in some tests we hit space limits for the VMs used as
        runners - being more aggressive about clearing out the bext
        source and build dirs from configure-driven builds to limit space
        consumption.
    4.  CPack - the new trick CPack was taught to bundled bext in src
        for package_source builds is murderous on hard disk space, since
        CMake isn't efficient and makes one copy of everything for each
        archive type - see https://gitlab.kitware.com/cmake/cmake/-/issues/16249
        Probably need to make our own alternative to package_source using
        cmake -E tar so we can avoid more than one copying setup stage...
    
    It's looking like the bext find logic (and BRL-CAD's for that matter)
    may need a bit more work - a couple of Ubuntu dependency installs didn't
    seem to result in the bext build skipping those components...

