commit ad83e9653e92f2cad63a3ae77388a2e521199107
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Sat Apr 13 08:36:41 2024 -0400

    Update to latest upstream detria

commit ed6b9392eef59c6ae126f29bf713b8304fc60f84
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Fri Apr 12 22:39:22 2024 -0400

    Add ifdef guarded tessellation code using detria
    
    The detria header-only implementation of CDT is looking very
    interesting.  Upstream changes made it work for a C++17 build, so add it
    to the build for more extensive testing, guarded by a USE_DETRIA ifdef
    check.
    
    Have tried a few simple cases - facetize of a brep rcc, shaded drawing
    of a few NURBS brep objects - but will need *extensive* testing to
    verify it works as we need it to, which is why it's added behind an
    ifdef conditional.  If this does pan out however, it would allow us to
    remove our older, semi-forked poly2tri version in favor of a new
    header-only implementation that is much simpler to integrate.  Upstream
    testing results suggest it may also be somewhat faster.

