commit ce3fe55b66385f3f53f2f66f425c88aa62267a26
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Fri Mar 29 14:44:35 2024 -0400

    Stash an rle version of the Tk test teapot img
    
    It's looking as if we didn't hook UtahRLE conversion support into
    libicv, which means we don't currently have the ability to read and
    write them exposed in our tools - need to fix that.
    
    rle images aren't common, so we create one by using the netpbm utility
    pnmtorle to convert the Tk test image of the teapot, and then passed
    that result through the old Utahrle tools rletoraw and rawtorle.  Using
    the netpbm rletopnm to convert the result back into something viewable
    indicates the conversions were sane, so this should at least give us
    something to work with.  Also add the original Tk version of the image
    (which is already in our repo history anyway via Tk) to use as a
    control.  In principle we ought to be able to read these both in with
    libicv and get a clean diff comparison.

commit 894cc62c38cf6e0e06459f15ef25eea0477805bb
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Fri Mar 29 14:11:11 2024 -0400

    With the new bext logic, modularlize/localize find
    
    misc/CMake/BRLCAD_ExternalDeps.cmake holds the find_package logic for
    the bext components, but for a modular build we don't want to be doing
    all the find_package calls right away.  If some components are disabled
    we never need to look for their dependencies at all.
    
    To make this work, we define macros that encapsulate what is needed for
    a resettable find process for each package (we use macros rather than
    functions deliberately here, otherwise the function scope encapsulates
    the find_package output variables and we would have to PARENT_SCOPE
    export the ones we care about - that's possible, but for now it's extra
    work and we can do it later if it looks like it would be beneficial.)
    
    The new macros are then called in the subdirectories where those
    packages are actually needed/used.  Because the scope of the
    find_package results isn't global except for variables being written to
    the cache, we call the macros separately in the various places we need
    them, but that should be acceptable - the results should always be the
    same, and the extra work of repeating the finds is minimal compared to
    the overall build and modularity benefits.
    
    This lets us build (for example) librt and its dependencies with:
    
    cmake .. -DBRLCAD_COMPONENTS=librt && make -j3
    
    If we let the BRL-CAD cmake configure also do its own bext build, it
    will try to enable only the bext dependencies needed for the active
    configuration (a pre-supplied bext, on the other hand, is what it is -
    the logic will not try to pick and choose just the files needed from an
    already created output directory, as there is no way to reliably tell
    what is needed and what isn't.)
    
    The next step is probably to look at whether it makes sense to push the
    various configure checks for headers and functions down closer to where
    they are needed as well.  That would probably mean revisiting
    brlcad_config.h - we'd either need to define private headers for the
    various individual libs and programs to use instead, or supply command
    line defines (the latter might make more sense if we only have a small
    number of defines relevant to a particular component.)  Would also need
    to determine which parts of brlcad_config.h really need to be part of
    the install, and which parts are build-time only.

commit 2a2f0995be3b4c14dc2857024a2826c33b1a540a
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Fri Mar 29 09:15:52 2024 -0400

    Make sure to list the common.h directory as well

