commit bac25b8e0bcc1d4904f88482554a5f7f80708483
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Tue Mar 26 17:15:20 2024 -0400

    Use BEFORE for most of the local target_include_directories additions.

commit 57eada581b92a4a33ee2e9c9d5bc38d6c718bea7
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Tue Mar 26 16:45:20 2024 -0400

    Do header sorting in per-target assignment setup
    
    We don't want to give up the preferential ordering we had established
    for our local headers with the previous include scheme, so rather than
    using generator expressions (which offer no opportunity to arrange
    the order of accumulated headers) we read the target properties and
    build up include lists that can be sorted at configure time.
    
    Probably worth examining more closely which headers end up in public and
    private groupings - not sure manifold and poly2tri need to be in public,
    for example - but for now this builds.
    
    TODO: Individual additions to the exec includes probably should be
    specifying the BEFORE property to make sure they receive preferential
    ordering, unless we're locally adding a system find_package result...

commit 9550739f1ca71e8fa6fba5c54dd48b99636541cb
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Tue Mar 26 15:43:17 2024 -0400

    Let BRLCAD_ADDEXEC and the target properties do most of the work of propagating the includes

commit 45e07f46a31d14cb6d2d22c1fce5bf29a0e288fc
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Tue Mar 26 13:19:12 2024 -0400

    Remove debugging messages, explain use of SYSTEM with INTERFACE_INCLUDE_DIRECTORIES

commit d565fe020efa1dcdd548b36331409c31dfe9853f
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Tue Mar 26 13:13:10 2024 -0400

    Rework BRLCAD_ADDLIB to use target_include_dirs
    
    Modern CMake practice uses target properties for include dirs, rather
    than per-directory includes.  This is a significant change to the
    BRL-CAD CMake logic, so start in a contained fashion with BRLCAD_ADDLIB.
    
    The idea is to propagate the interface includes of dependencies using
    these properties, rather than having to explicitly list them out.  Logic
    should be more compact overall, as well as letting us more precisely
    target include dirs to their intended targets even when there are
    multiple targets defined in one directory.

commit 3357887874e180c7fa72cf1015efc40df6687bfb
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Tue Mar 26 08:46:31 2024 -0400

    Blegh - forget it, just pass in the options explicitly.

