commit a64773a124841560e10bb5ca10530a91b50698c4
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Fri Mar 22 17:29:11 2024 -0400

    Can probably key the mann pages off of libged, but the man1 pages are a different story...

commit a7dfef176a1e8cc10363117767b3525fcfef6475
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Fri Mar 22 17:21:01 2024 -0400

    Test mechanism to optionally require targets to build man pages
    
    This will need some thought, since we originally consolidated the man
    page targets to avoid exploding the target count in Visual Studio, but
    to support a cleaner modular build we need to avoid building man pages
    or things that have been disabled.
    
    One possibility might be to handle the Docbook building right in the
    BRLCAD_ADDEXEC and/or plugin functions and make them part of the main
    exec/plugin build.

