commit b4f28c8cb86bc3eb52c7f082f9a15f9f0a952179
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Thu Mar 21 15:16:35 2024 -0400

    Prototype a more modularized build approach
    
    Instead of the three levels previously defined, explore supporting
    specifying one or more "components" of BRL-CAD to be enabled.  The idea
    would be that if a user defines (say) -DBRLCAD_COMPONENTS=librt then
    only librt and its dependencies would be enabled for compilation.
    
    For this to be properly realized a lot of higher level build logic will
    have to be conditionalized based on whether various targets are
    available (for example, regression tests will need to be disabled if
    their executables aren't defined as targets) but this should let us be
    way more flexible when it comes to "only build what we want" situations.

commit acb3fccff7842ed50370a87a8370376489927e86
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
