    Merge branch 'main' into facetize

commit 04b73749f90cb49fb579b5954078aedbb82163a9
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Tue Mar 19 21:33:36 2024 -0400

    Update behavior of dbconcat command's prefix/suffix application
    
    Previously, when the user suffied a prefix or suffix string to dbconcat,
    it would always apply the prefix and suffix to all incoming object
    names, regardless of whether the incoming name conflicted with any
    object already in the database.  While there are potential scenarios
    where this property is useful - it is one potential way to identify
    objects that came from the concated database - it is a hinderance when
    the goal is to merge the incoming geometry with a minimum of renaming
    but using less generic alteration strings than the default no
    prefix/suffix dbconcat naming behavior.
    
    What we do if a user prefix/suffix is specified by default is to only
    use it for renaming if we need to in order to resolve a naming conflict.
    If the user wishes to have the previous "always applied" behavior, they
    can get it by adding the -A option flag along with the prefix/suffix
    option.
    
    The initial motivation for this is the use of the new facetize command
    implementation's region mode, which operates on a working copy and then
    dbconcats the result back into the original file.  We want to prefix the
    copies of the top level combs, but not (unless necessary) the new BoT
    solid primitives, which usually will have no corresponding conflicting
    object in the original file.

commit 56d2d45f50418a4babf3274c73ed249e4dc90dc4
Author: Clifford Yapp <238416+starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Tue Mar 19 20:46:36 2024 -0400

    Fix comment typo

